column1: Please follow the instructions carefully and ensure that information is accurate properly assigned and formatted.
You will be presented with the error list (if any) and you will have the option to download the file, fix the errors and re-upload.
You will always have the option to fix any assignment mistakes one at a time by logging into your account.
INSTRUCTIONS
Allowed file format : Comma-separated CSV.
If you do not wish to setup a particular line, simply delete the corresponding row.
Extension numbers can be edited, but must be unique to each user.
Required fields can not be left blank.
Emergency Service Address can not be PO Box. It will be validated.
Emergency Service Address fields are required if DL = yes.
Enter user name against the desired phone number and phone make/model row.
Choose your preferred User Language which used to view your account and notifications. E.g. English US (en_US), English UK (en_GB) or Canadian French (fr_CA).
DO NOT make any changes to the first 5 columns and cells in the table that are greyed-out
DO NOT change the order of columns
DO NOT use commas in your data if you use CSV format
DO NOT delete any columns. DO NOT add any new columns
DO NOT setup more than 1000 users at once
